The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                            The City Diary
                A 59-year-old man was was knocked down by a minibus on Strand Road on Wednesday afternoon. Pradip Mukherjee, a resident of Uttarpara, was taken to Medical College and Hospital with multiple injuries in the head and face, said an official.    A fire broke out at Barrackpores Meghna Jute Mill early on Wednesday, damaging goods worth nearly a crore. According to fire brigade officials, the blaze broke out in the batching section of the mill during the morning shift. Four labourers were injured. Firemen said the blaze might have started from a short-circuit in the bare electrical lines.    Bibek Majumder, 32, was hit by a bus carrying call centre employees at Jatragachi, on New Town Road, on Wednesday afternoon. Police said Majumder, an employee of a local library, was crossing the road on his bicycle when the bus, headed for Salt Lake, hit him. He was admitted to Bidhannagar Sub-divisional Hospital.    A youth, in his mid-20s, was arrested on BB Ganguly Street, in Bowbazar, on Wednesday. Police seized a firearm from Adil Iqbal, the accused. An interrogation revealed that he was roaming in the area with the intention of snatching valuables from pedestrians at gun-point.     State finance minister Asim Dasgupta laid the foundation stone of a residential school for blind girls at 37/2 Bhairab Dutta Lane, in Howrah, on Wednesday. The school and the hostel will be built on 1.66 acres.    Environmentalist Subhas Dutta on Wednesday demanded that the government come up immediately with clear guidelines on the use of parks. He also urged the government to complete Milon Mela, the permanent fairground off the EM Bypass, at the earliest.                                                                                                                                                                
